Yes, there are open source libraries that allow you to generate PDF files from HTML in .NET Core. One such library is wkhtmltopdf, which is a command line tool that uses the WebKit rendering engine to convert HTML to PDF. You can use the library by invoking the command line tool from your .NET Core application using the Process class.

Here's an example of how you can use wkhtmltopdf in your .NET Core application to generate a PDF from HTML:

1. First, you need to download and install wkhtmltopdf from the official website: <https://wkhtmltopdf.org/downloads.html>. Choose the appropriate version for your operating system and architecture.
2. Once you've installed wkhtmltopdf, you can call it from your .NET Core application using the Process class. Here's an example:
```csharp
using System.Diagnostics;

// ...

var html = "<html><body><h1>Hello, world!</h1></body></html>";
var fileName = "output.pdf";

var startInfo = new ProcessStartInfo
{
    FileName = "wkhtmltopdf",
    Arguments = $"- -q \"{fileName}\"",
    RedirectStandardInput = true,
    UseShellExecute = false
};

using (var process = new Process { StartInfo = startInfo })
{
    process.Start();

    using (var streamWriter = process.StandardInput)
    {
        streamWriter.WriteLine(html);
    }

    process.WaitForExit();
}
```
In this example, we're passing the HTML as input to wkhtmltopdf using standard input, and specifying the output file name using the command line argument `-q`.

